{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770048587,"nonce":"ympRw3mYx8EwjkdG+VxZv/wjJVU=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87nq114","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/125","origin":"github"},"title":"Feature: Enforce Agent Isolation via Task Wrapper","message":"**Problem**\nAgents (and users) sometimes default to working in the main source tree instead of creating worktrees, risking workspace pollution and conflicts in a multi-agent environment (as seen in PR #115 work). The current \"option\" to use worktrees is not strong enough enforcement.\n\n**Proposed Solution**\nCreate a unified `agent` CLI entry point that enforces isolation:\n*   **Command**: `agent start-task \u003cissue-id\u003e [repo]`\n*   **Behavior**:\n    1.  Automatically creates a worktree for the task (following Issue #122 naming conventions).\n    2.  Enters the worktree.\n    3.  Sets up the environment.\n*   **Enforcement**: Agents should be instructed to *only* start work via this command.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**\n- [ ] `agent` wrapper script created.\n- [ ] `start-task` subcommand automates worktree creation and entry.\n- [ ] \"Native\" checkout usage is discouraged in documentation.\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Antigravity Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Gemini 3 Pro (High)`","files":null}]}